by carlcs at 2019-06-07T07:40:48Z

For inspiration, in Craft CMS we've got a `attr()` function ([see docs](https://github.com/craftcms/cms/blob/3.2/docs/dev/functions.md#attr)).

```twig
{% set myAttributes = {
    class: ['one', 'two'],
    disabled: true,
    readonly: false,
    data: {
        baz: 'Escape this "',
        qux: {
            some: ['data', '"quoted"']
        }
    },
    style: {
        'background-color': 'red',
        'font-size': '20px'
    },
} %}

<div {{ attr(myAttributes) }}></div>
```

For conditional classes you can use ternary notation in the array.

```twig
{% set myAttributes = {
    class: [
        'one',
        loop.last ? 'two',
    ],
} %}

<div {{ attr(myAttributes) }}></div>
```

If `class` is the only attribute you want to output.

```twig
{% set class = [
    'one',
    loop.last ? 'two',
] %}

<div {{ attr({ class: class }) }}></div>
```

Another great use case where I would love to see shorthand notation for object props become a thing in Twig. Maybe one dayâ€¦ https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/pull/3002

